Malwarebytes Labs has released a report on a device which can unlock any Apple iPhone. The device is called the GrayKey, and is made by a company called Grayshift – from the US. The GrayKey – a small box with two lighting cables sticking out from it – is reportedly aimed at law enforcement agencies and is a turn-key solution. It reportedly works as follows: Once the device is “unlocked”, its contents can be downloaded to the GrayKey and accessed through a web interface on a PC. Malwarebytes Labs said the GrayKey works on the latest iPhones and up to at least iOS 11.2.5. The top-of-the-range GrayKey sells for $30,000. 